feat: wire Docker monitoring state transitions into event ingest pipeline (fl-c71)

Add internal/dockermon package that polls monitored containers via Docker
Engine API over Unix socket, tracks health state (healthy/degraded/down),
and fires OnStateChange callback on transitions.

Wire in main.go gated on FAULTLINE_DOCKER_SOCKET env var. The callback
creates events with platform:'docker', fingerprint
sha256('dockermon|{container_name}|{check_type}'), level mapped from
state, and title format 'Docker {service}: {check} — {message}'.
Events flow through handler.ProcessCIEvent into the standard ingest
pipeline, making existing alert rules, integrations, and Gas Town bead
filing work automatically.

